{
  "id": 5100036528275456,
  "name": "ScrollIntoView container option",
  "summary": "The ScrollIntoViewOptions container option allows developers to perform a scrollIntoView only scrolling the nearest ancestor scroll container. For example, the following snippet only scrolls the scroll container of target to bring target into view, but will not scroll all of the scroll containers to the viewport:\r\n\r\ntarget.scrollIntoView({container: 'nearest'});",
